    {
      "content": "{\n  \"cwd\": \"/Users/sam.zhang/Documents/codex-supervisor\",\n  \"execution_layer_policy\": {\n    \"agentic_lead_policy\": {\n      \"min_subagents\": 0,\n      \"policy\": \"off\",\n      \"required_evidence_grade\": \"self_reported\",\n      \"required_roles\": [],\n      \"solo_exception_for_artifact_only_gates\": false\n    },\n    \"allowed_dynamic_workflow_task_classes\": [],\n    \"codex_supervises_final_artifact\": true,\n    \"dynamic_workflow_task_class\": null,\n    \"lead_execution_layer\": \"single_lead_worker\",\n    \"mode\": \"lead_direct\",\n    \"preview_required_gates\": [],\n    \"supervision_layer\": \"codex_plus_lead\"\n  },\n  \"expected_decisions\": [],\n  \"expected_objections\": [],\n  \"expected_specialists\": [],\n  \"gate\": \"outcome_review\",\n  \"instruction\": \"Supervisor-owned workflow gate: outcome_review.\\n\\nIntent:\\nConvert the SINGLE independent-reviewer slot into a provenance-preserving reviewer PANEL as one schema/API change that adds independent_reviewer_results[] (N reviewers, full per-reviewer metadata), introduces the independent_reviewer_review event kind, and keeps full backward compatibility with legacy single-slot cursor_review / tri_agent_cursor_review. Build it behind a thin reviewer-registry interface validated with mock reviewers and the real working Gemini/litellm_structured reviewer. Do not block on a second vendor and do not change the gate decision yet. Acceptance: schema exposes independent_reviewer_results[]; today's reviewer appears as element 0 with runtime, lineage, assurance_grade, transcript refs, hashes, severity, confidence; registry yields reviewers and is exercised with mock and Gemini/litellm_structured path; new independent_reviewer_review events are emitted and legacy tri_agent_cursor_review events still read/export/replay; gate decision unchanged versus current main on representative run; ADR committed; deterministic replay preserved; full suite green; ledger and replay artifacts exported.\\n\\nReview this gate against the current source artifacts and return a typed dual_agent_outcome.\\nUse decisions/objections to say whether the gate should accept, revise, or deny.\",\n  \"lead_skill\": null,\n  \"outcome_validation_policy\": {\n    \"fidelity_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"malformed_outcome\": \"retry_once_with_corrective_packet\",\n    \"subprocess_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"timeout\": \"abort_to_operator\"\n  },\n  \"packet_schema_version\": \"dual-agent-handoff/v1\",\n  \"planning_artifacts\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"prd\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-panel-foundation-20260601/source/prd.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"34261e206e9b776f6da37b817fb41f20919050bf1289a94868fd7655ece740fb\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"grill_findings\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-panel-foundation-20260601/source/grill-findings.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"52b7978687626d8f93d284abed8015c98395f233fb762242324ab6e93005bd80\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"issues\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-panel-foundation-20260601/source/issues.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"9087e4a165dadb701937c50264dea294ee5c358273d124aba1592173449ff5d6\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"tdd_plan\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-panel-foundation-20260601/source/tdd.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"6a033ee77dffaeb7ae0b23fb328a8a55cd066f893ad2f8b63d866c1c2387f09a\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"grill_findings\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-panel-foundation-20260601/source/grill-findings-tdd.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"80aae9fc82dfe422dfa4401efd74c55c47acbac736aeccb34eddd1fcd21981aa\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"implementation_plan\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/d